# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Verified and confirmed that Vercel Web Analytics is properly installed and configured for this React + Vite project according to the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Current Implementation Status
✅ **Already Complete** - The project already has Vercel Web Analytics fully configured and working.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/analytics@2.0.1` (latest version)
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Status**: Already installed in package.json and package-lock.json is up to date

### 2. Analytics Component Integration
- **File**: `Frontend/src/App.jsx`
- **Import**: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
- **Placement**: `<Analytics />` component added at the end of the App component, inside the AppShell wrapper
- **Implementation**: Follows the official React/Vite documentation exactly as specified

### 3. Framework Configuration
- **Framework**: React 18.3.1 with Vite 5.4.10
- **Integration Method**: React component approach (recommended for React/Vite projects)
- **Location**: Placed in the root App component to track all pages and routes

