## Code Implementation

The Analytics component is correctly integrated in `src/App.jsx`:

```jsx
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";

function App() {
  const location = useLocation();

  return (
    <AppShell>
      <AnimatePresence mode="wait">
        <Routes location={location} key={location.pathname}>
          {/* All routes */}
        </Routes>
      </AnimatePresence>
      <Analytics />
    </AppShell>
  );
}
```

## Documentation Reference
Implementation follows the official Vercel Web Analytics Quickstart guide for React projects:
- Source: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Method: React component integration
- Import path: `@vercel/analytics/react`

## Next Steps
No further action required. The implementation is complete and ready for deployment. When deployed to Vercel:
1. Analytics data will automatically start collecting
2. View data in the Vercel Dashboard under the Analytics tab
3. Verify setup by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/view`

## Notes
- The Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact page load performance
- Data collection respects user privacy and GDPR compliance
- Analytics will only be active when deployed to Vercel (not in local development)
- No additional configuration or API keys are required
